g.text: 1. as a user, i can create a budget for track something that i want ( food, transporation )
2. as a user, i can create expense and mark it to budget that been created #1
3. as a user, i can get the expense list as a table
4. as a user, i can get the budget list, and how much left
5. as a user, i can register account and sign in
1. as a user, i can the notification if my expense exceed budget ( each category )
2. as a user, i can upload the photo / media to the expense created
5. Persistency: Data will be stores for 5 years
2. Read per seconds: 100 * 10 WPS = 1000 Read per seconds
- For 5 years expense is 3 times budget: 7TB * 3 = 21TB
as a user, i can register account and sign in
Here i will designing register and login flow, based on criteria above
1. User will calls /v1/register with their email & password
2. Our load balancer will distribute the request
3. We have 3 replicas of webserver that has rate limiter in it
4. The server will move the request to the user service
5. The user service will hash the password
6. User service will insert to the database
7. User service will execute email service to notify the user to verified email
1. User will calls /v1/login with their email & password
2. Our load balancer will distribute the request
3. We have 3 replicas of webserver that has rate limiter in it
4. The server will move the request to the user service
5. The user service will fetch the user from database
6. We will compare if the passsword match or not
